IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Location: 233 Wineland Way, Stevensville, Maryland Incident Date 09/19/2023 Narrative: On September 25, 2023 I received cybertip 174722155 from the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children (NCMEC). The cybertip was submitted through the cybertip line by a private individual. The following information was provided with the cybertip. Submitter: Taylor Not Say Not say Gender: Male Contact: Yes IP Address: 137.103.83.190 Received by NCMEC on 09-23-2023 Primary Incident Type: Child Pornography (possession, manufacture, and distribution) Additional Incident Type: Misleading Words or Digital Images on the Internet Incident Time: 09-19-2023 14:59:00 UTC Ongoing Incident: Yes Incident Date Range: Yesterday / Today / Now Reason the reporter/child victim may be in physical danger: I sent a photo and made me pay her 100$ to delete it so I paid now she wants more and I dontknow what to do we are texting through iMessage through her email flexjanes183@gmail.com No further identifying information or return contact information was provided in the cybertip. The IP address was searched through open-source IP address geolocators and found to be an Breezeline, Inc. IP address. A subpoena was sent to Breezeline through the Queen Annes County States Attorneys Office. On October 9, 2023 I received the requested information from Breezeline. SUBSCRIBER INFORMATION Subscriber Name: Lisa Atkins Subscriber Address: 233 Wineland Way, Stevensville, MD, 21666 Account Activation Date: 06/24/2020 Account Deactivation Date: Account is still active. A preservation request was sent to Google for the account Flexjanes183@gmail.com. Case remains open pending contact with the residence.

On October 16, 2023 I met with the victim Taylor Atkins (hereafter referred to as Taylor), and his mother, Lisa Atkins (hereafter referred to as Lisa) at their residence at 233 Wineland Way, Stevensville, MD, 21666. Taylor told me he met the suspect on a social media application known as Wizz. After speaking with the suspect they moved the conversation to text messages. Taylor said the suspect used the email account flexjanes183@gmail.com to message him. The suspect asked him to send nude images of himself, which he did, and then demanded he pay $100 or she would send the pictures to his friends. He said he went to the nearby Target and got gift cards to send. After he sent the gift cards the suspect attempted to get more money from him and he blocked the account. He said the suspect attempted to contact him with different accounts but he kept blocking them. A safety talk was conducted with Taylor and Lisa and they were provided with additional information on safe internet usage. At this time the case will be closed by a safety talk. Case status: Closed.
